title: For Sale:  IMR 7828 SSC 1 Lb Keg
postcontent:
For sale is one 1 LB keg of IMR 7828 SSC.  The 7828 brand was designed as a big magnum powder.  The slow burning provides real magnum performance in the large over bored magnums such as the .300 Remington Ultra Mag, .30-378 Weatherby Magnum and the 7MM Remington Ultra Magnum.  IMR 7828 SSC magnum rifle powder has the exact same burn rate as standard IMR 7828 and uses the same data.  However, due to the super short kernels, metering is virtually as good as a spherical powder.  This allows up to 4% more powder space in the case and in many loads yields more velocity than standard 7828.  These loads are marked with an asterisk in the IMR data to show where standard 7828 will not fit.

title: For Sale:  Buffalo Bore Ammo - .45 ACP +P Ammo - 230 gr. J.H.P. (950 fps/M.E. 461 ft. lbs.) - 50 Round Box
postcontent:
http://extreme-impact-ammo.com/index.php?l=product_detail&p=68

45ACP+P ammo is externally/dimensionally identical to 45 ACP ammo and can be fired in any 45 acp firearm that is in normal operating condition. However, the greater pressures and power of the +P ammo will give you greater slide velocity and if you are going to shoot more than a box or two of +P ammo, you should consider replacing your recoil spring with a Wolf Spring that gives roughly 4 to 6 lbs more spring weight than factory stock springs. A shock buffer might also be a good addition although it is not too necessary if you use the stronger spring.


The below velocities were fired from my personal Colt Gold Cup 1911 (5 inch)


1. 45185-----------1180 fps (185gr. Jhp)
2. 45200-----------1078 fps (200gr. Jhp)
3. 45230------------979 fps (230gr. Jhp)
4. 45230FMJ------981 fps (230gr. Fmj-FLAT NOSE)
5. 45255------------960 fps  (255gr. HARD CAST-FLAT NOSE)


As always, with Buffalo Bore Ammunition, we use real world firearms to give real world data and results. Laboratory test barrels tell you little about what kind of speed you can expect from your stock firearm.

All our 45 ACP+P loads utilize flash suppressed powders so that you will not be blinded by your own gunfire should you need to fire in the dark when the criminal element is at work.


The three JHP loads are design for defense against humans, while the two non-expanding loads are designed to shoot through large shoulder bones or the skull on a black bear. These non-expanding bullets also work well if you need to shoot through cover like car doors or stick frame walls.

It has a skeletonized polished striker pin that has maritime spring cups on it. It has brand new Trijicon night sights, and the front sight tool. title: For Sale:  Hand Engraved Double Barrel Shotgun
postcontent: I have a Hand Engraved German Double Barrel Shotgun.  Proofed in September of 1925.  The German Gun Collectors Association believes this is what is known as an "apprentice" gun.  It was likely made in the town of Suhl.  An apprentice gun is a "final exam" for an apprentice under a master gunsmith.  This is a 16 gauge 2 9/16" chamber.  It is Nitro proofed so modern 2 3/4" shells work just fine.  I shot most of a box to make sure everything worked.  One firing pin stuck a little.  I put some oil down in there and the problem cleared up.  Beautiful hand engraving on every metal surface of this gun.  There is some wear to the engraving.  It was used as a hunting gun for Quail for some time.  There is a makers mark on the gun, but the Collectors association did not have notes for the mark.  That's why it is believed to be an apprentice gun.  Apprentice guns usually run half as much as a noted maker.  That puts this gun in the $1,500 range.  Hopefully a maker can be found out by the mark someday!  Cash Only, No Trades.  $1,200 OBO
